.TH man 5 "11 Sep 2014" "1.2" "LDMS Plugin meminfo man page"

.SH NAME
Plugin_meminfo - man page for the LDMS meminfo plugin

.SH SYNOPSIS
Within ldmsctl
.br
ldmsctl> config name=meminfo [ <attr>=<value> ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
With LDMS (Lightweight Distributed Metric Service), plugins for the ldmsd (ldms daemon) are configured via ldmsctl.
The meminfo plugin provides memory info from /proc/meminfo.

.SH LDMSCTL CONFIGURATION OPTIONS

.TP
.BR config
name=<plugin_name> component_id=<comp_id> set=<set_name> 
.br
ldmsctl configuration line
.RS
.TP
<plugin_name>
.br
This MUST be meminfo.
.TP
<comp_id>
.br
The component id numerical value.
.TP
<set_name>
.br
The name of the metric set.
.RE

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.nf
.RS
$/tmp/opt/ovis/sbin/ldmsctl -S /var/run/ldmsd/metric_socket_vm1_1
ldmsctl> load name=meminfo
ldmsctl> config name=meminfo component_id=1 set=vm1_1/meminfo
ldmsctl> start name=meminfo interval=1000000
ldmsctl> quit

.SH SEE ALSO
ldmsctl(8), Plugin_cray_system_sampler(5), Plugin_lustre2_client(5), Plugin_kgnilnd(5), Plugin_procnetdev(5), Plugin_procsensors(5), 
Plugin_procstatutil(5), Plugin_procnfs(5), Plugin_sysclassib(5), Plugin_vmstat(5)

.SH BUGS
